parse: Personal / Relative Pronoun - Accusative Feminine Singular

str2: A city, the inhabitants of a city. Probably from the same as polemos, or perhaps from polus; a town.
Or, than. A primary particle of distinction between two connected terms; disjunctive, or; comparative, than.
A village, country town. From keimai; a hamlet.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To go in, come in, enter. From eis and erchomai; to enter.

parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To examine, question, inquire at, search out. From ek and etazo; to test thoroughly, i.e. Ascertain or interrogate.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
Worthy, worthy of, deserving, comparable, suitable. Probably from ago; deserving, comparable or suitable.

parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To remain, abide, stay, wait; with acc: I wait for, await. A primary verb; to stay.
And there, and yonder, there also. From kai and ekei; likewise in that place.
A conjunction, preposition and adverb of continuance, until.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To go out, come out. From ek and erchomai; to issue.
